#. <section class="sutta" id="sn4.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.2:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. Life Span"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 2. Hatthirājavaṇṇasutta → nāgasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3) | nāgo (pts1)
msgctxt "sn4.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Hatthirājavaṇṇasutta"
msgstr "2. In the Form of an Elephant King"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.104"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.233"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.2:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn4.2:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā uruvelāyaṃ viharati najjā nerañjarāya tīre "
"ajapālanigrodhamūle paṭhamābhisambuddho."
msgstr ""
"At one time, when he was first awakened, the Buddha was staying near Uruvelā "
"at the root of the goatherd’s banyan tree on the bank of the Nerañjarā River."

# At SN 41.4 such a rain was regarded as pleasantly cooling.
msgctxt "sn4.2:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā rattandhakāratimisāyaṃ abbhokāse nisinno "
"hoti, devo ca ekamekaṃ phusāyati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the Buddha was meditating in the open during the dark of "
"night, while a gentle rain drizzled down."

msgctxt "sn4.2:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā bhagavato bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃsaṃ uppādetukāmo "
"mahantaṃ hatthirājavaṇṇaṃ abhinimminitvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked, wanting to make the Buddha feel fear, terror, and "
"goosebumps, manifested in the form of a huge elephant king and approached "
"him."

msgctxt "sn4.2:1.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma mahāariṭṭhako maṇi;"
msgstr "Its head was like a huge block of soapstone."

msgctxt "sn4.2:1.6"
msgid "evamassa sīsaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.2:1.7"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma suddhaṃ rūpiyaṃ;"
msgstr "Its tusks were like pure silver."

msgctxt "sn4.2:1.8"
msgid "evamassa dantā honti."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: naṅgalīsā → naṅgalasīsā (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn4.2:1.9"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma mahatī naṅgalīsā;"
msgstr "Its trunk was like a long plough pole."

msgctxt "sn4.2:1.10"
msgid "evamassa soṇḍo hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.2:1.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāya "
"ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, addressed him in "
"verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.2:2.1"
msgid "“Saṃsaraṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ,"
msgstr "“Transmigrating for such a long time,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.2:2.2"
msgid "Vaṇṇaṃ katvā subhāsubhaṃ;"
msgstr "you’ve made forms beautiful and ugly."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.2:2.3"
msgid "Alaṃ te tena pāpima,"
msgstr "Enough of this, Wicked One!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.2:2.4"
msgid "Nihato tvamasi antakā”ti."
msgstr "You’re beaten, terminator!”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.2:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā “jānāti maṃ bhagavā, jānāti maṃ sugato”ti dukkhī "
"dummano tatthevantaradhāyīti."
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The Buddha knows me! The Holy One knows me!”"
" miserable and sad, vanished right there."
